[8] USA (Virginia, Washington DC, Maryland)
Date: Wed 21 May 2014
Source: WUSA-9 [edited]
http://www.wusa9.com/story/news/local/2014/05/21/measles-exposure-dc-maryland-virginia/9370117/


Health officials are investigating potential exposure to measles in Northern Virginia, Washington DC, and Montgomery County [Maryland] after a 2nd person was confirmed to have measles. The exposures occurred between [11 and 15 May 2014] at locations in Fairfax County, Loudoun County, and Arlington County, Virginia, Montgomery County, Maryland, and the District [of Columbia]. This effort expands the recent investigation of a measles case in late April 2014 in Loudoun and Fairfax Counties [Virginia].

The 2nd case of measles was confirmed in a person who was a close contact of the 1st case, officials say. Officials say the investigation is being conducted out of an abundance of caution. [20 specific locations and times, where local residents may have been exposed to infection are listed in this press report and available at the source URL above. - Mod.CP]

