[10] Russia (Altai Republic, Novosibirsk Oblast)
Date: Mon 19 May 20114
Source: 1NSK-RU News [in Russian, trans. Mod.CP, edited]
http://1nsk.ru/news/novosibirsk/39494.html


Two dozen residents of the Altai Republic have contracted measles, the 1st cases in the Republic for a period of 12 years. This is not yet regarded as threatening by epidemiologists in Novosibirsk, but they are warning local practitioners that they should not relax vigilance in view of the fact that Novosibirsk is a transit point for all the neighbouring republics.

Vaccination against the disease is included in the national immunisation calendar, administered ay one year and 6 years of age. However, it is possible to be vaccinated at a later age and adults up to 35 years of age can be vaccinated. Doctors warn that the infection is transmitted by airborne droplets.

Larissa Pozdnjakova, chief epidemiologist for the Novosibirsk region stated, "This infection is very contagious. You cannot ignore a single contact, and because the clinical manifestations develop very rapidly there is not time for delay."

--
