[11] Russia (Altai Republic)
Date: Sun 18 May 2014
Source: Altai Mountains News [in Russian, trans. Mod.CP, edited]
http://www.gorno-altaisk.info/news/29731


Already 32 people including 3 children in the Altai Republic have been hospitalized with measles. Nonetheless the authorities claim that the situation is under control. The local residents have been requested to comply with preventive measures, and at the 1st signs of infection (fever, rash, cough, runny nose) to seek medical attention. The last previous case in Altai Republic was registered in 2001, and the country's last major outbreak of measles occurred 2 years ago when 1500 cases were registered from 48 regions.

